    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces, then peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>peeled garlic</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, bring to the boil and cook over a high heat for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub the <strong>steak[s]</strong> with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>steak[s]</strong> and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through</p><p>Reboil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced green beans </strong>and <strong>carrot batons</strong> to a pot, cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until tender, then drain and return to the pot until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> wholegrain mustard </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> mustard stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork steak is cooked through (no pink meat!), transfer to a chopping board or shallow plate, cover with a clean tea towel and leave to rest until serving</p><p>Reserve the pan and any<strong> pork juices</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>mustard stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Increase the heat to medium-high, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened to creamy consistency</p><p>Once thickened, remove from the heat and stir in the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>pork juices</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>mustard sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> <strong>&</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> to a low heat with a knob of<strong> butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-steak-with-garlic-mash-and-mustard-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork loin steak</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>mustard sauce</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>green beans</strong>, <strong>carrot batons </strong>and<strong> garlic mash</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
